query error raw_dl\(\) requires an inverted index scan in the same sub-query
SELECT id, raw_dl(docs.tableoid) FROM docs WHERE id > 0;


query
EXPLAIN SELECT id, raw_dl(docs_idx.tableoid) FROM docs_idx
WHERE body @@ ts_phrase('fox') ORDER BY id;
----
QUERY PLAN
┌───────────────────────────┐
│          ORDER_BY         │
│    ────────────────────   │
│      docs_idx.id ASC      │
│                           │
│          ~0 rows          │
└─────────────┬─────────────┘
┌─────────────┴─────────────┐
│       IRESEARCH_SCAN      │
│    ────────────────────   │
│      Index: docs_idx      │
│      Lookup: rocksdb      │
│                           │
│          Filter:          │
│ AND[PHRASE[body(string) = │
│    <Term:fox(0, 0); >]]   │
│                           │
│      Score: raw_dl()      │
│                           │
│        Projections:       │
│             id            │
│  sdb_inverted_index_score │
│                           │
│          ~5 rows          │
└───────────────────────────┘



query error Only one scorer function is allowed per inverted index
